I pushed on to Los Angeles--and was sorry to learn that the cinemacompany I had counted upon was about to fold after Ivor Black's death. On myway back, in early spring, I rediscovered the dear phantasmata of mychildhood in the tender green of aspen groves at high altitudes here andthere, on conifer-clothed ridges. For almost six months I roamed again frommotel to motel, several times having my car scratched and cracked bycretinous rival drivers and finally trading it in for a sedate Bel